This paper is about the fifth reactive synthesis competition, which is a competition focused on formal methods and automated synthesis of correct-by-construction systems. The paper discusses the evaluation scheme and experimental setup of the competition, as well as the results and ranking of the participating tools. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), which covers topics related to formal methods, automated reasoning, and logic-based approaches to computer science. Other likely sub-categories include cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these areas also have a strong focus on formal methods and automated reasoning.
